messages.content:
The document outlines a project proposal for a "Reverse Car Parking System and Automatic Speed Control." The main deliverable is a system designed to assist drivers in parking their electric vehicles (EVs) by using audio-visual signals and incorporating automatic speed control to reduce accident risks during prolonged reversing.

**Key Components:**
- Raspberry Pi (Broadcom BCM2711, Quadcore Cortex-A72)
- 7” display compatible with Raspberry Pi 3/4
- L293D motor IC for motor control
- HCSR-04 ultrasound sensor
- 2MP Pi camera
- Jumper cables and custom motor driver PCB

**Objective:** To develop a reverse parking system with automatic speed control for the institute’s EV car.

**Team Members:**
1. Abhinav Tripathi (Roll No. 230957)
2. Karmanya Bhalla (Roll No. 230864)

The proposal includes a brief description of the project, emphasizing its functionality and safety features.
